# User Registration Business Validation Flow (Duplicate Record):

01. User ne form submit kiya aur input validation successfully pass ho gayi.

02. Request UserRegistrationCtl ke doPost() method me aayi.

03. doPost() method me populateBean(request) view ka data get kiya or UserBean me set kiya.
    UserBean bean = (UserBean) populateBean(request);

04. UserModel ka object banaya gaya:
    UserModel model = new UserModel();

05. model.add(bean) method call kiya gaya.

06. UserModel.add() method me sabse pehle existing record check kiya gaya:
    UserBean existbean = findByLogin(bean.getLogin());

07. findByLogin() method database me query chala kar check karti hai ki same login id already exist karti hai ya nahi. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}

08. Agar existbean null nahi hai (matlab login already exist karta hai) to:
    throw new DuplicateRecordException("Login Id already exists");

09. Ye exception wapas UserRegistrationCtl ke doPost() method me catch hoti hai.

10. catch (DuplicateRecordException e) block me:
    - ServletUtility.setBean(bean, request) call hota hai
    - ServletUtility.setErrorMessage("Login id already exists", request) set kiya jata hai

11. Uske baad:
    ServletUtility.forward(getView(), request, response) call hota hai

12. Request wapas UserRegistration.jsp par forward hoti hai.

13. JSP par:
    ServletUtility.getErrorMessage(request) se "Login id already exists" message show hota hai.
